  "texts": [
    "Image tiles can be extracted from slides, processed and stain normalized, and predictions are generated for each tile from a slide.",
    "The final slide-level prediction is the average prediction from all tiles.",
    "Tile-level predictions can be visualized as a heatmapDuring training, images can undergo augmentation to broaden the training domain and promote generalizability (Fig. 1C).",
    "Images can undergo random cardinal rotation and random horizontal or vertical flipping, random JPEG compression, 5 and random Gaussian blur, 6 and stain augmentation.",
    "When using Tensorflow, images are standardized to a mean of 0 and standard deviation of 1, and when using PyTorch, images are standardized to a range of 0-1.By default, mini-batch balancing is used to ensure equal representation of all slides in each batch and equal representation of all classes (Additional file 1: Fig. 2)."
